<title type="html"><![CDATA[Unskippable cut scenes]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6471&amp;p=62515#p62515"><![CDATA[
For what it's worth, I'm in agreement with Disch here.  Making cutscenes or drama-scenes (think Ninja Gaiden) skippable is more or less a requirement.  If the player/user wants to skip said scenes, they'll press a button/whatever.  If they don't, that's their choice too.  If the scene in question is actually a training sequence and they skip it, so what -- it's their own fault/demise.<br /><br />The modus operandi for not permitting cutscene skipping seems to be either paranoia or vengeance; I can't tell which.<br /><br />Do you know how many NES and SNES games I've played where I've skipped tutorials, cut-scenes, etc. simply to get back to the gameplay -- instead referring to the user manual for details?  Many.  :-)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3">koitsu</a> — Sun Jun 06, 2010 8:50 am</p><hr />
