<div class="quotetitle">UncleSporky wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Enlighten me, because I see no arguments against this.<br /></div><br /><br />It wasn't an argument against it so much as it was an offer of alternatives.  If the controls of a game are unclear or unintuitive, a "how to play" or a "tutorial" menu option at the title screen would be a wise decision.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />How do you know people are likely to refuse?  All I know from this topic is the anecdotal report of one Disch who would refuse.  According to my own anecdotal research, everyone else I know would watch the scene.<br /></div><br /><br />Well if they're unlikely to refuse then what are we even talking about?<br /><br />The whole "cutscenes might contain important info" was brought up as a counter point to illustrate why cutscenes shouldn't necessarily be skippable.  If people aren't likely to skip them, then it's a moot point.<br /><br />I will say, however, that everyone I know IRL cares very little for in game cutscenes and just want to play the game.  I think only the hardcore gamer nerds (no offense) really care, and these days that makes up a rather small percentage of all gamers.<br /><br />But again, speculation.  I can't prove that.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />I'm not intentionally alienating anyone<br /></div><br /><br />I think I'm getting my wires crossed by arguing too many tangents at once.<br /><br />I'll admit defeat on most points.  The point I stand by is this:<br /><br />There is no reason for a game to refuse to make the cutscene skippable.  Players often want to skip them, it costs nothing to make them skippable, they don't have to be skipped, etc, etc.<br /><br />Those who want to skip them can, and those who don't want to don't have to.  It's win-win for everyone.  Everyone gets what they want out of the game.<br /><br />It should always be an option in any game with any kind of cutscene.  Failure to put it in is a major design flaw.<br /><br />I stand by this.<br /><br />Cave Story, in particular, suffers from this in an extreme way.  To the point where I don't even want to play it anymore, even though I still find the game part of it fun.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">There is absolutely no reason those cutscenes shouldn't have been skippable.  It was a terrible design decision to make them nonskippable.<br /></div><br />As there is no objective measurement for quality in a game, one man's serious flaw is another's favorite part.  You have no right to call anything a flaw unless you keep in mind that you don't speak for anyone else.</div><br /><br />That would make sense if I were talking about an aspect of the gameplay.<br /><br />I'm talking about the cutscenes not being skippable.<br /><br />Are you honestly going to tell me that people like a game more because it <em>doesn't</em> give you an option to make the cutscenes skippable?  Because that's a bogus claim and you know it.  If they like the cutscenes, they can still watch them, even if they're skippable.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Wrong according to one Disch.<br />[snip]<br />People who skip the scene before it have no right to complain when they get shot in the chest after they choose "skip."<br /></div><br /><br />Fine, you're right.<br /><br />I disagree with your design ideas.  I think there are better, more interesting, and more dynamic ways to inform the player of their in game surroundings than solely putting things in cutscenes.  I've mentioned some of ideas of how it could easily be accomplished in this thread.<br /><br />I also think that games which use these other methods are better for it,  are less likely to frustrate (and therefore alienate) the player, and are therefore designed better.<br /><br />But that is just one man's opinion.  I'll concede that it's not fact.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=33">Disch</a> — Sun Jun 06, 2010 8:39 am</p><hr />
